### Create a Deployment

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/deployments" \
-X POST \
-H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
-H "Content-type: application/json" \
-d '{
  "droplet": {
    "guid": "[droplet-guid]"
  },
  "relationships": {
    "app": {
      "data": {
        "guid": "[app-guid]"
      }
    }
  }
}'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 201 OK
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :single_deployment %>
```

#### Definition
`POST /v3/deployments`

#### Required Parameters

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | -----------
**app** | [_to-one relationship_](#to-one-relationships) | The app to deploy a droplet for.

#### Optional Parameters

Name | Type | Description | Default
---- | ---- | ----------- | -------
**droplet** | _object_ | The droplet to deploy for the app. This will update the app's [current droplet](#get-current-droplet-association-for-an-app) to this droplet | The app's [current droplet](#get-current-droplet-association-for-an-app)

